cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a new method for generating object and action proposals in images and videos using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The method also involves selecting the most promising locations and refining them in a coarse-to-fine manner, which suggests the involvement of machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also evaluates the proposed method's performance using metrics such as recall and detection performance, indicating the involvement of multimedia and information retrieval techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) possible sub-categories.
